Package net.objectzoo.events.impl

This package contains support classes that implement EventDelegates ready to be used.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
DynamicEventAsyncDelegate An DynamicEventAsyncDelegate implements DynamicActionAsync as well as DynamicEventDelegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the DynamicActionAsync interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the DynamicEventDelegate interface.
DynamicEventDelegate An DynamicEventDelegate implements DynamicAction as well as DynamicEvent and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the DynamicAction interface to all subscribers of the DynamicEvent interface.
Event0AsyncDelegate An Event0AsyncDelegate implements Action0Async as well as Event0Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action0Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event0Delegate interface.
Event0Delegate An Event0Delegate implements Action0 as well as Event0 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action0 interface to all subscribers of the Event0 interface.
Event2AsyncDelegate<T1,T2> An Event2AsyncDelegate implements Action2Async as well as Event2Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action2Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event2Delegate interface.
Event2Delegate<T1,T2> An Event2Delegate implements Action2 as well as Event2 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action2 interface to all subscribers of the Event2 interface.
Event3AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3> An Event3AsyncDelegate implements Action3Async as well as Event3Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action3Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event3Delegate interface.
Event3Delegate<T1,T2,T3> An Event3Delegate implements Action3 as well as Event3 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action3 interface to all subscribers of the Event3 interface.
Event4AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3,T4> An Event4AsyncDelegate implements Action4Async as well as Event4Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action4Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event4Delegate interface.
Event4Delegate<T1,T2,T3,T4> An Event4Delegate implements Action4 as well as Event4 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action4 interface to all subscribers of the Event4 interface.
EventAsyncDelegate<T> An EventAsyncDelegate implements ActionAsync as well as EventDelegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the ActionAsync interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the EventDelegate interface.
EventDelegate<T> An EventDelegate implements Action as well as Event and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action interface to all subscribers of the Event interface.
 

Class Summary
DynamicEventAsyncAdapter The DynamicEventAsyncAdapter is class that adapts an DynamicEventDelegate to DynamicEventAsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
DynamicEventCaller The DynamicEventCaller is a DynamicEventDelegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
DynamicEventDistributor The DynamicEventDistributor is a DynamicEventDelegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers.
Event0AsyncAdapter The Event0AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event0Delegate to Event0AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
Event0Caller The Event0Caller is a Event0Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
Event0Distributor The Event0Distributor is a Event0Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers.
Event2AsyncAdapter<T1,T2> The Event2AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event2Delegate to Event2AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
Event2Caller<T1,T2> The Event2Caller is a Event2Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
Event2Distributor<T1,T2> The Event2Distributor is a Event2Delegate implementation allows that event distribution to multiple subscribers.
Event3AsyncAdapter<T1,T2,T3> The Event3AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event3Delegate to Event3AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
Event3Caller<T1,T2,T3> The Event3Caller is a Event3Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
Event3Distributor<T1,T2,T3> The Event3Distributor is a Event3Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers.
Event4AsyncAdapter<T1,T2,T3,T4> The Event4AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event4Delegate to Event4AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
Event4Caller<T1,T2,T3,T4> The Event4Caller is a Event4Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
Event4Distributor<T1,T2,T3,T4> The Event4Distributor is a Event4Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers.
EventAsyncAdapter<T> The EventAsyncAdapter is class that adapts an EventDelegate to EventAsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
